<title>USA: Silicon Valley settles Mentor lawsuit.</title>
<headline>Silicon Valley settles Mentor lawsuit.</headline>
<dateline>SAN JOSE, Calif. 1997-02-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Silicon Valley Research said Friday it reached full settlement of a lawsuit brought against the company by Mentor Graphics Corp.</p>
<p>The settlement includes the exchange of, and certain rights to, specified technology.  Also, Silicon Valley will issue about 600,000 shares of its common stock, it said.</p>
<p>The company said there will be no impact to its operating results for the current quarter from the settlement because it had provided for all estimated costs associated with the settlement.  Further details of the settlement terms were not immediately available.</p>
